Python Home
===========

Place for Python libraries installed by the current user. To make it work you
have to override prefix in ~/.pydistutils.cfg and put a home.pth file in the
Python site-packages direcotory with the following contents:

    import os, site; site.addsitedir(os.path.expanduser('~/.python/lib/python2.5/site-packages'))

More information can be found in the documentation:

    http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/EasyInstall#custom-installation-locations
    http://docs.python.org/install/index.html#install-index
